        <div class='post' itemprop='articleBody'>
          <p>What the fuck is with your hate for Halo Reach.</p>
<p>It’s right up there with Halo: Combat Evolved. The amount of online customisation when it comes to game modes is mind blowing. Couple that with a fun SP campaign, decent graphics and awesome weaponry and you have yourself a helluva game.</p>
<p>Playing the SP campaign in co-op on Legendary was some of the most fun I’ve had as a gamer.</p>
<p>Also, “little gameplay variety.” Have you even played all the different game modes in Reach. There’s tons of variety.</p>
<p>And the gameplay flows so well in Reach maps.</p>
<p>Jesus Christ!</p>
<p>EDIT: And on the subject of Black Ops, whilst it didn’t bring much new content or gameplay, it was very refined and improved on a lot of issues that plagued MW2. Kill streak stacking was finally removed and the addition of a Theatre mode was great.</p>
<p>I only played it for about 10 or so hours, then went back to Borderlands and BFBC2 Vietnam.</p>
        </div>

